missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/selector.md:14:Chain 01 stays in because it is the highest-upside route in the run and the only branch that can turn a successful audit into a true compactness-rigidity program rather than a local mechanism memo. Its failure mode is also useful: the chain is disciplined enough to say whether the first fatal break is extraction, formulation, definability of the rigidity quantity, or non-coercivity.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/selector.md:22:Chain 04 is the best surviving geometry reboot, but it is the weakest of the four on expected value. Its first likely breaks are transport persistence, localization debt, and outside-region strain freedom, which means it is more exposed to dying before it reaches a criterion-scale statement. It is genuinely different, but the selected set already achieves strong diversity across global compactness, exact symbolic algebra, and tensorial stretching analysis while keeping a better balance of upside and useful failure output.
