missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/selected/chain-01.md:29:### Step 2 - Define the hypothetical minimal blowup object in the chosen framework
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/selected/chain-01.md:32:- Action: state the minimizing quantity, solution class, symmetry group, normalization conventions, and the exact compactness or almost-periodicity statement the extraction package would deliver.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/selected/chain-01.md:38:### Step 3 - Screen rigidity quantities only on the actual critical-element class
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/selected/chain-01.md:41:- Action: list candidate rigidity quantities or identities that are well-defined on the Step 2 class.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/selected/chain-01.md:42:- Action: for each candidate, record the contradiction mechanism, the stability under compactness limits, the nearest prior-art overlap, and whether Tao's averaged model appears to destroy the relevant feature.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/selected/chain-01.md:43:- Action: reject any candidate that is undefined on the class, unstable under the compactness limit, already absorbed by a known non-operative template, or cosmetic in the chosen architecture.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/selected/chain-01.md:44:- Expected output: one promoted rigidity quantity and at most one backup, each with a short mechanism statement.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/selected/chain-01.md:45:- Kill condition: if no candidate survives definability, non-cosmeticity, and mechanism screening, stop and write a rigidity obstruction.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/selected/chain-01.md:50:- Action: run the promoted rigidity quantity through the critical element and state the contradiction pathway line by line, including where compactness, almost periodicity, pressure structure, and solution-class regularity enter.
