missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/mission-context.md:433:Chain 03 has a serious upside tail, but its likely positive path is still weakly credible relative to the system burden it imposes. The refined version improved the sequencing, yet the branch remains dominated by foundational compactness, coercive-backbone, and rigidity difficulties. It is more likely to produce an obstruction map than an actionable program, and its execution demands are less concrete than Chain 02's.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/mission-context.md:666:Chain 03 is the strongest high-upside alternative, but it is still more credible as a compactness-and-rigidity obstruction audit than as a live positive attack. The setup burden is much larger, the theorem-compatibility risks are heavier, and the branch can absorb significant effort before identifying whether the route is circular.
