missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:5:The attacker is mostly right. The original chain had a good anti-hand-waving instinct, especially its refusal to juggle many spaces and many rigidity ideas at once, but it allowed too many soft deliverables and asked for a rigidity choice too early. The strongest corrections are:
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:8:- define the hypothetical critical element before overcommitting to one rigidity mechanism;
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:12:The attack overstates one point: the compactness-rigidity pivot is not illegitimate just because it is familiar. The problem was not the general template. The problem was that the original chain had not yet made the template executable in a Navier-Stokes-specific way.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:20:This lands cleanly. A ranking of `L^3`, `\dot H^{1/2}`, and `BMO^{-1}` is not enough. The branch should require one host space to clear a concrete ledger:
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:27:- a compactness notion usable by the later rigidity step.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:31:### 2. Step 2 uses placeholder rigidity ideas and overweights Tao-sensitivity
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:35:The original levers were categories, not mechanisms. Also, "unavailable to Tao's averaged model" is too weak to serve as a hard admission criterion. It can still be used as a secondary filter, but only after a candidate quantity is shown to be defined on the actual compactness class and to offer a concrete contradiction mechanism.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:37:### 3. The chain chooses rigidity too early and should formulate the critical object first
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:41:This sequencing objection is correct. The hypothetical critical element determines what regularity, compactness, pressure control, and normalization are actually available. Those facts should discipline rigidity selection. The refined chain therefore moves critical-object formulation ahead of final rigidity promotion.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:53:The original "first missing NS-specific lemma" idea was directionally good but under-specified. The refined chain now requires that the first missing lemma be strictly narrower than arbitrary finite-energy regularity and use the compactness-normalized class in an essential way. It also distinguishes failure modes:
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:55:- rigidity quantity not closed under the compactness limit;
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:58:- no contradiction even under almost periodicity.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/judgments/chain-02.md:77:The novelty critique is fair: without a usable Navier-Stokes rigidity quantity, the original chain overlaps heavily with the standard critical-element playbook. But the pivot itself is still defensible as a planning branch because the mission only needs a presentable result, not a proof breakthrough. A disciplined obstruction map can be valuable if it identifies the first fatal break precisely. So the right repair is not to discard the chain, but to make its outputs harsher and less aesthetic.
