missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-05.md:5:The exact tensor identities of NS may contain information that averaged quadratic models do not retain at the same level. The key objects are the strain tensor, the pressure Hessian, and the vorticity-stretching identity `omega . grad u = S omega`. This chain tests whether eigenframe dynamics or sign structure in these tensors yields a usable rigidity or conditional criterion.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-05.md:16:This chain is tensorial rather than geometric or compactness-based. It does not assume vortex tubes and does not hunt for a new commutator; it asks whether the exact NS tensor algebra itself is the missing structural property.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/mission-context.md:66:2. **Profile decomposition / concentration-compactness.** Kenig-Merle type approach: assume blowup, extract critical element, derive contradiction. Works for energy-critical NLS. For NS: supercriticality makes critical element extraction harder. Gallagher-Koch-Planchon (2016) have partial results.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/mission-context.md:433:- **Best execution fit for this system:** it can be driven by explicit objects, scenario classes, localization protocols, and kernel-level representations. That is a better match for disciplined stepwise analysis than the heavier global compactness-and-rigidity audit in Chain 03.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/mission-context.md:444:Chain 03 has a serious upside tail, but its likely positive path is still weakly credible relative to the system burden it imposes. The refined version improved the sequencing, yet the branch remains dominated by foundational compactness, coercive-backbone, and rigidity difficulties. It is more likely to produce an obstruction map than an actionable program, and its execution demands are less concrete than Chain 02's.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/mission-context.md:677:Chain 03 is the strongest high-upside alternative, but it is still more credible as a compactness-and-rigidity obstruction audit than as a live positive attack. The setup burden is much larger, the theorem-compatibility risks are heavier, and the branch can absorb significant effort before identifying whether the route is circular.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-03.md:16:This is the only chain built around coherent structures and high-vorticity geometry. It does not seek a new norm inequality or a new compactness theorem.
